HEADWORD: Diethylamine
<hw>Di*eth`yl*am"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>ethylamine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
colorless, volatile, alkaline liquid, <chform>NH(C2H5)2</chform>, having
a strong fishy odor resembling that of herring or sardines. Cf.
<er>Methylamine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

